{
  "texts": [
    "Rather than the Utilitarianism being offered by AI influencers who seek funding for their companies, one must follow the Aristotelian logic and account for what is best for humans, within the existing lawful system and directives.",
    "Probably, the current law system is old and incomplete and needs a revision to face the new challenges.",
    "Some will even claim that probably it is already too late to catch up with all this exponential progress of the past five years in AI, but it is a necessary step that must be done in order to be able to help our civilization towards the ethical technological elevation of humanity.",
    "It is clear, that in a diverse and multipolar world such as the one that is unraveling before us, the guidelines that the Aristotelian framework offers in regulating AI are the way forward.",
    "Namely, cultivating virtue for the individual and the society, aiming for the golden mean between two extremes, understanding the Telos (purpose) of the function of AI systems, Phronesis and Eudemonia of humans and society; and finally, categorization and taxonomy of individual AI systems with explainability and interpretability of their decisions."
  ]
}